ieee802dot11.description: The MIB module for IEEE 802.11 entities. iso(1).member-body(2).us(840).ieee802dot11(10036)

dot11StationConfigTable.name: dot11StationConfigTable
dot11StationConfigTable.description: Station Configuration attributes. In tablular form to allow for multiple instances on an agent.

dot11StationConfigEntry.name: dot11StationConfigEntry
dot11StationConfigEntry.description: An entry in the dot11StationConfigTable. It is possible for there to be multiple IEEE 802.11 interfaces on one agent, each with its unique MAC address. The relationship between an IEEE 802.11 interface and an interface in the context of the Internet-standard MIB is one-to-one. As such, the value of an ifIndex object instance can be directly used to identify corresponding instances of the objects defined herein. ifIndex - Each IEEE 802.11 interface is represented by an ifEntry. Interface tables in this MIB module are indexed by ifIndex.

dot11StationID.name: dot11StationID
dot11StationID.description: The purpose of dot11StationID is to allow a manager to identify a station for its own purposes. This attribute provides for that eventuality while keeping the true MAC address independent. Its syntax is MAC address, and the default value is the station's assigned, unique MAC address.

dot11MediumOccupancyLimit.name: dot11MediumOccupancyLimit
dot11MediumOccupancyLimit.description: This attribute shall indicate the maximum amount of time, in TU, that a point coordinator (PC) may control the usage of the wireless medium (WM) without relinquishing control for long enough to allow at least one instance of DCF access to the medium. The default value of this attribute shall be 100, and the maximum value shall be 1000.

dot11CFPollable.name: dot11CFPollable
dot11CFPollable.description: When this attribute is true, it shall indicate that the STA is able to respond to a CF-Poll with a data frame within a SIFS time. This attribute shall be false if the STA is not able to respond to a CF-Poll with a data frame within a SIFS time.

dot11CFPPeriod.name: dot11CFPPeriod
dot11CFPPeriod.description: The attribute shall describe the number of DTIM intervals between the start of CFPs. It is modified by MLME-START.request primitive.

dot11CFPMaxDuration.name: dot11CFPMaxDuration
dot11CFPMaxDuration.description: The attribute shall describe the maximum duration of the CFP in TU that may be generated by the PCF. It is modified by MLME-START.request primitive.

dot11AuthenticationResponseTimeOut.name: dot11AuthenticationResponseTimeOut
dot11AuthenticationResponseTimeOut.description: This attribute shall specify the number of time units (TUs) that a responding STA should wait for the next frame in the authentication sequence.

dot11PrivacyOptionImplemented.name: dot11PrivacyOptionImplemented
dot11PrivacyOptionImplemented.description: This attribute, when true, shall indicate that the IEEE 802.11 WEP option is implemented. The default value of this attribute shall be false.

dot11PowerManagementMode.name: dot11PowerManagementMode
dot11PowerManagementMode.description: This attribute shall specify the power management mode of the STA. When set to active, it shall indicate that the station is not in power-save (PS) mode. When set to powersave, it shall indicate that the station is in power-save mode. The power management mode is transmitted in all frames according to the rules in 7.1.3.1.7.

dot11DesiredSSID.name: dot11DesiredSSID
dot11DesiredSSID.description: This attribute reflects the Service Set ID (SSID) used in the DesiredSSID parameter of the most recent MLME_Scan.request. This value may be modified by an external management entity and used by the local SME to make decisions about the Scanning process.

dot11DesiredBSSType.name: dot11DesiredBSSType
dot11DesiredBSSType.description: This attribute shall specify the type of BSS the station shall use when scanning for a BSS with which to synchronize. This value is used to filter Probe Response frames and Beacons. When set to infrastructure, the station shall only synchronize with a BSS whose Capability Information field has the ESS subfield set to 1. When set to independent, the station shall only synchronize with a BSS whose Capability Information field has the IBSS subfield set to 1. When set to any, the station may synchronize to either type of BSS.

dot11OperationalRateSet.name: dot11OperationalRateSet
dot11OperationalRateSet.description: This attribute shall specify the set of data rates at which the station may transmit data. Each octet contains a value representing a rate. Each rate shall be within the range from 2 to 127, corresponding to data rates in increments of 500 kbit/s from 1 Mbit/s to 63.5 Mbit/s, and shall be supported (as indicated in the supported rates table) for receiving data. This value is reported in transmitted Beacon, Probe Request, Probe Response, Association Request, Association Response, Reassociation Request, and Reassociation Response frames, and is used to determine whether a BSS with which the station desires to synchronize is suitable. It is also used when starting a BSS, as specified in 10.3.

dot11BeaconPeriod.name: dot11BeaconPeriod
dot11BeaconPeriod.description: This attribute shall specify the number of TUs that a station shall use for scheduling Beacon transmissions. This value is transmitted in Beacon and Probe Response frames.

dot11DTIMPeriod.name: dot11DTIMPeriod
dot11DTIMPeriod.description: This attribute shall specify the number of beacon intervals that shall elapse between transmission of Beacons frames containing a TIM element whose DTIM Count field is 0. This value is transmitted in the DTIM Period field of Beacon frames.

dot11AssociationResponseTimeOut.name: dot11AssociationResponseTimeOut
dot11AssociationResponseTimeOut.description: This attribute shall specify the number of TU that a requesting STA should wait for a response to a transmitted association-request MMPDU.

dot11DisassociateReason.name: dot11DisassociateReason
dot11DisassociateReason.description: This attribute holds the most recently transmitted Reason Code in a Disassociation frame. If no Disassociation frame has been transmitted, the value of this attribute shall be 0.

dot11DisassociateStation.name: dot11DisassociateStation
dot11DisassociateStation.description: This attribute holds the MAC address from the Address 1 field of the most recently transmitted Disassociation frame. If no Disassociation frame has been transmitted, the value of this attribute shall be 0.

dot11DeauthenticateReason.name: dot11DeauthenticateReason
dot11DeauthenticateReason.description: This attribute holds the most recently transmitted Reason Code in a Deauthentication frame. If no Deauthentication frame has been transmitted, the value of this attribute shall be 0.

dot11DeauthenticateStation.name: dot11DeauthenticateStation
dot11DeauthenticateStation.description: This attribute holds the MAC address from the Address 1 field of the most recently transmitted Deauthentication frame. If no Deauthentication frame has been transmitted, the value of this attribute shall be 0.

dot11AuthenticateFailStatus.name: dot11AuthenticateFailStatus
dot11AuthenticateFailStatus.description: This attribute holds the most recently transmitted Status Code in a failed Authentication frame. If no failed Authentication frame has been transmitted, the value of this attribute shall be 0.

dot11AuthenticateFailStation.name: dot11AuthenticateFailStation
dot11AuthenticateFailStation.description: This attribute holds the MAC address from the Address 1 field of the most recently transmitted failed Authentication frame. If no failed Authentication frame has been transmitted, the value of this attribute shall be 0.

dot11MultiDomainCapabilityImplemented.name: dot11MultiDomainCapabilityImplemented
dot11MultiDomainCapabilityImplemented.description: This attribute, when TRUE, indicates that the station implementation is capable of supporting multiple regulatory domains. The capability is disabled, otherwise. The default value of this attribute is FALSE.

dot11MultiDomainCapabilityEnabled.name: dot11MultiDomainCapabilityEnabled
dot11MultiDomainCapabilityEnabled.description: This attribute, when TRUE, indicates that the capability of the station to operate in multiple regulatory domains is enabled. The capability is disabled, otherwise. The default value of this attribute is FALSE.

dot11CountryString.name: dot11CountryString
dot11CountryString.description: This attribute identifies the country in which the station is operating. The first two octets of this string is the two character country code as described in document ISO/IEC 3166-1. The third octet shall be one of the following: 1. an ASCII space character, if the regulations under which the station is operating encompass all environments in the country, 2. an ASCII 'O' character, if the regulations under which the station is operating are for an Outdoor environment only, or 3. an ASCII 'I' character, if the regulations under which the station is operating are for an Indoor environment only.

dot11AuthenticationAlgorithmsTable.name: dot11AuthenticationAlgorithmsTable
dot11AuthenticationAlgorithmsTable.description: This (conceptual) table of attributes shall be a set of all the authentication algorithms supported by the stations. The following are the default values and the associated algorithm: Value = 1: Open System Value = 2: Shared Key

dot11AuthenticationAlgorithmsEntry.name: dot11AuthenticationAlgorithmsEntry
dot11AuthenticationAlgorithmsEntry.description: An Entry (conceptual row) in the Authentication Algorithms Table. ifIndex - Each IEEE 802.11 interface is represented by an ifEntry. Interface tables in this MIB module are indexed by ifIndex.

dot11AuthenticationAlgorithmsIndex.name: dot11AuthenticationAlgorithmsIndex
dot11AuthenticationAlgorithmsIndex.description: The auxiliary variable used to identify instances of the columnar objects in the Authentication Algorithms Table.

dot11AuthenticationAlgorithm.name: dot11AuthenticationAlgorithm
dot11AuthenticationAlgorithm.description: This attribute shall be a set of all the authentication algorithms supported by the STAs. The following are the default values and the associated algorithm. Value = 1: Open System Value = 2: Shared Key

dot11AuthenticationAlgorithmsEnable.name: dot11AuthenticationAlgorithmsEnable
dot11AuthenticationAlgorithmsEnable.description: This attribute, when true at a station, shall enable the acceptance of the authentication algorithm described in the corresponding table entry in authentication frames received by the station that have odd authentication sequence numbers. The default value of this attribute shall be 1 for the Open System table entry and 2 for all other table entries.

dot11WEPDefaultKeysTable.name: dot11WEPDefaultKeysTable
dot11WEPDefaultKeysTable.description: Conceptual table for WEP default keys. This table shall contain the four WEP default secret key values corresponding to the four possible KeyID values. The WEP default secret keys are logically WRITE-ONLY. Attempts to read the entries in this table shall return unsuccessful status and values of null or zero. The default value of each WEP default key shall be null.

dot11WEPDefaultKeysEntry.name: dot11WEPDefaultKeysEntry
dot11WEPDefaultKeysEntry.description: An Entry (conceptual row) in the WEP Default Keys Table. ifIndex - Each IEEE 802.11 interface is represented by an ifEntry. Interface tables in this MIB module are indexed by ifIndex.

dot11WEPDefaultKeyIndex.name: dot11WEPDefaultKeyIndex
dot11WEPDefaultKeyIndex.description: The auxiliary variable used to identify instances of the columnar objects in the WEP Default Keys Table. The value of this variable is equal to the WEPDefaultKeyID + 1

dot11WEPDefaultKeyValue.name: dot11WEPDefaultKeyValue
dot11WEPDefaultKeyValue.description: A WEP default secret key value.

dot11WEPKeyMappingsTable.name: dot11WEPKeyMappingsTable
dot11WEPKeyMappingsTable.description: Conceptual table for WEP Key Mappings. The MIB supports the ability to share a separate WEP key for each RA/TA pair. The Key Mappings Table contains zero or one entry for each MAC address and contains two fields for each entry: WEPOn and the corresponding WEP key. The WEP key mappings are logically WRITE-ONLY. Attempts to read the entries in this table shall return unsuccessful status and values of null or zero. The default value for all WEPOn fields is false.

dot11WEPKeyMappingsEntry.name: dot11WEPKeyMappingsEntry
dot11WEPKeyMappingsEntry.description: An Entry (conceptual row) in the WEP Key Mappings Table. ifIndex - Each IEEE 802.11 interface is represented by an ifEntry. Interface tables in this MIB module are indexed by ifIndex.

dot11WEPKeyMappingIndex.name: dot11WEPKeyMappingIndex
dot11WEPKeyMappingIndex.description: The auxiliary variable used to identify instances of the columnar objects in the WEP Key Mappings Table.

dot11WEPKeyMappingAddress.name: dot11WEPKeyMappingAddress
dot11WEPKeyMappingAddress.description: The MAC address of the STA for which the values from this key mapping entry are to be used.

dot11WEPKeyMappingWEPOn.name: dot11WEPKeyMappingWEPOn
dot11WEPKeyMappingWEPOn.description: Boolean as to whether WEP is to be used when communicating with the dot11WEPKeyMappingAddress STA.

dot11WEPKeyMappingStatus.name: dot11WEPKeyMappingStatus
dot11WEPKeyMappingStatus.description: The status column used for creating, modifying, and deleting instances of the columnar objects in the WEP key mapping Table.

dot11PrivacyTable.name: dot11PrivacyTable
dot11PrivacyTable.description: Group containing attributes concerned with IEEE 802.11 Privacy. Created as a table to allow multiple instantiations on an agent.

dot11PrivacyEntry.name: dot11PrivacyEntry
dot11PrivacyEntry.description: An entry in the dot11PrivacyTable Table. ifIndex - Each IEEE 802.11 interface is represented by an ifEntry. Interface tables in this MIB module are indexed by ifIndex.

dot11PrivacyInvoked.name: dot11PrivacyInvoked
dot11PrivacyInvoked.description: When this attribute is true, it shall indicate that the IEEE 802.11 WEP mechanism is used for transmitting frames of type Data. The default value of this attribute shall be false.

dot11WEPDefaultKeyID.name: dot11WEPDefaultKeyID
dot11WEPDefaultKeyID.description: This attribute shall indicate the use of the first, second, third, or fourth element of the WEPDefaultKeys array when set to values of zero, one, two, or three. The default value of this attribute shall be 0.

dot11WEPKeyMappingLength.name: dot11WEPKeyMappingLength
dot11WEPKeyMappingLength.description: The maximum number of tuples that dot11WEPKeyMappings can hold.

dot11ExcludeUnencrypted.name: dot11ExcludeUnencrypted
dot11ExcludeUnencrypted.description: When this attribute is true, the STA shall not indicate at the MAC service interface received MSDUs that have the WEP subfield of the Frame Control field equal to zero. When this attribute is false, the STA may accept MSDUs that have the WEP subfield of the Frame Control field equal to zero. The default value of this attribute shall be false.

dot11WEPICVErrorCount.name: dot11WEPICVErrorCount
dot11WEPICVErrorCount.description: This counter shall increment when a frame is received with the WEP subfield of the Frame Control field set to one and the value of the ICV as received in the frame does not match the ICV value that is calculated for the contents of the received frame.

dot11WEPExcludedCount.name: dot11WEPExcludedCount
dot11WEPExcludedCount.description: This counter shall increment when a frame is received with the WEP subfield of the Frame Control field set to zero and the value of dot11ExcludeUnencrypted causes that frame to be discarded.

dot11Disassociate.name: dot11Disassociate
dot11Disassociate.description: The disassociate notification shall be sent when the STA sends a Disassociation frame. The value of the notification shall include the MAC address of the MAC to which the Disassociation frame was sent and the reason for the disassociation. ifIndex - Each IEEE 802.11 interface is represented by an ifEntry. Interface tables in this MIB module are indexed by ifIndex.

dot11Deauthenticate.name: dot11Deauthenticate
dot11Deauthenticate.description: The deauthenticate notification shall be sent when the STA sends a Deauthentication frame. The value of the notification shall include the MAC address of the MAC to which the Deauthentication frame was sent and the reason for the deauthentication. ifIndex - Each IEEE 802.11 interface is represented by an ifEntry. Interface tables in this MIB module are indexed by ifIndex.

dot11AuthenticateFail.name: dot11AuthenticateFail
dot11AuthenticateFail.description: The authenticate failure notification shall be sent when the STA sends an Authentication frame with a status code other than 'successful'. The value of the notification shall include the MAC address of the MAC to which the Authentication frame was sent and the reason for the authentication failure. ifIndex - Each IEEE 802.11 interface is represented by an ifEntry. Interface tables in this MIB module are indexed by ifIndex.

dot11MultiDomainCapabilityTable.name: dot11MultiDomainCapabilityTable
dot11MultiDomainCapabilityTable.description: This (conceptual) table of attributes for cross-domain mobility.

dot11MultiDomainCapabilityEntry.name: dot11MultiDomainCapabilityEntry
dot11MultiDomainCapabilityEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) in the Multiple Domain Capability Table. IfIndex - Each IEEE 802.11 interface is represented by an ifEntry. Interface tables in this MIB are indexed by ifIndex.

dot11MultiDomainCapabilityIndex.name: dot11MultiDomainCapabilityIndex
dot11MultiDomainCapabilityIndex.description: The auxiliary variable used to identify instances of the columnar objects in the Multi Domain Capability Table.

dot11FirstChannelNumber.name: dot11FirstChannelNumber
dot11FirstChannelNumber.description: This attribute shall indicate the value of the lowest channel number in the subband for the associated domain country string. The default value of this attribute shall be zero.

dot11NumberofChannels.name: dot11NumberofChannels
dot11NumberofChannels.description: This attribute shall indicate the value of the total number of channels allowed in the subband for the associated domain country string. The default value of this attribute shall be zero.

dot11MaximumTransmitPowerLevel.name: dot11MaximumTransmitPowerLevel
dot11MaximumTransmitPowerLevel.description: This attribute shall indicate the maximum transmit power, in dBm, allowed in the subband for the associated domain country string. The default value of this attribute shall be zero.

dot11OperationTable.name: dot11OperationTable
dot11OperationTable.description: Group contains MAC attributes pertaining to the operation of the MAC. This has been implemented as a table in order to allow for multiple instantiations on an agent.

dot11OperationEntry.name: dot11OperationEntry
dot11OperationEntry.description: An entry in the dot11OperationEntry Table. ifIndex - Each IEEE 802.11 interface is represented by an ifEntry. Interface tables in this MIB module are indexed by ifIndex.

dot11MACAddress.name: dot11MACAddress
dot11MACAddress.description: Unique MAC Address assigned to the STA.

dot11RTSThreshold.name: dot11RTSThreshold
dot11RTSThreshold.description: This attribute shall indicate the number of octets in an MPDU, below which an RTS/CTS handshake shall not be performed. An RTS/CTS handshake shall be performed at the beginning of any frame exchange sequence where the MPDU is of type Data or Management, the MPDU has an individual address in the Address1 field, and the length of the MPDU is greater than this threshold. (For additional details, refer to Table 21 in 9.7.) Setting this attribute to be larger than the maximum MSDU size shall have the effect of turning off the RTS/CTS handshake for frames of Data or Management type transmitted by this STA. Setting this attribute to zero shall have the effect of turning on the RTS/CTS handshake for all frames of Data or Management type transmitted by this STA. The default value of this attribute shall be 2347.

dot11ShortRetryLimit.name: dot11ShortRetryLimit
dot11ShortRetryLimit.description: This attribute shall indicate the maximum number of transmission attempts of a frame, the length of which is less than or equal to dot11RTSThreshold, that shall be made before a failure condition is indicated. The default value of this attribute shall be 7.

dot11LongRetryLimit.name: dot11LongRetryLimit
dot11LongRetryLimit.description: This attribute shall indicate the maximum number of transmission attempts of a frame, the length of which is greater than dot11RTSThreshold, that shall be made before a failure condition is indicated. The default value of this attribute shall be 4.

dot11FragmentationThreshold.name: dot11FragmentationThreshold
dot11FragmentationThreshold.description: This attribute shall specify the current maximum size, in octets, of the MPDU that may be delivered to the PHY. An MSDU shall be broken into fragments if its size exceeds the value of this attribute after adding MAC headers and trailers. An MSDU or MMPDU shall be fragmented when the resulting frame has an individual address in the Address1 field, and the length of the frame is larger than this threshold. The default value for this attribute shall be the lesser of 2346 or the aMPDUMaxLength of the attached PHY and shall never exceed the lesser of 2346 or the aMPDUMaxLength of the attached PHY. The value of this attribute shall never be less than 256.

dot11MaxTransmitMSDULifetime.name: dot11MaxTransmitMSDULifetime
dot11MaxTransmitMSDULifetime.description: The MaxTransmitMSDULifetime shall be the elapsed time in TU, after the initial transmission of an MSDU, after which further attempts to transmit the MSDU shall be terminated. The default value of this attribute shall be 512.

dot11MaxReceiveLifetime.name: dot11MaxReceiveLifetime
dot11MaxReceiveLifetime.description: The MaxReceiveLifetime shall be the elapsed time in TU, after the initial reception of a fragmented MMPDU or MSDU, after which further attempts to reassemble the MMPDU or MSDU shall be terminated. The default value shall be 512.

dot11ManufacturerID.name: dot11ManufacturerID
dot11ManufacturerID.description: The ManufacturerID shall include, at a minimum, the name of the manufacturer. It may include additional information at the manufacturer's discretion. The default value of this attribute shall be null.

dot11ProductID.name: dot11ProductID
dot11ProductID.description: The ProductID shall include, at a minimum, an identifier that is unique to the manufacturer. It may include additional information at the manufacturer's discretion. The default value of this attribute shall be null.

dot11CountersTable.name: dot11CountersTable
dot11CountersTable.description: Group containing attributes that are MAC counters. Implemented as a table to allow for multiple instantiations on an agent.

dot11CountersEntry.name: dot11CountersEntry
dot11CountersEntry.description: An entry in the dot11CountersEntry Table. ifIndex - Each IEEE 802.11 interface is represented by an ifEntry. Interface tables in this MIB module are indexed by ifIndex.

dot11TransmittedFragmentCount.name: dot11TransmittedFragmentCount
dot11TransmittedFragmentCount.description: This counter shall be incremented for an acknowledged MPDU with an individual address in the address 1 field or an MPDU with a multicast address in the address 1 field of type Data or Management.

dot11MulticastTransmittedFrameCount.name: dot11MulticastTransmittedFrameCount
dot11MulticastTransmittedFrameCount.description: This counter shall increment only when the multicast bit is set in the destination MAC address of a successfully transmitted MSDU. When operating as a STA in an ESS, where these frames are directed to the AP, this implies having received an acknowledgment to all associated MPDUs.

dot11FailedCount.name: dot11FailedCount
dot11FailedCount.description: This counter shall increment when an MSDU is not transmitted successfully due to the number of transmit attempts exceeding either the dot11ShortRetryLimit or dot11LongRetryLimit.

dot11RetryCount.name: dot11RetryCount
dot11RetryCount.description: This counter shall increment when an MSDU is successfully transmitted after one or more retransmissions.

dot11MultipleRetryCount.name: dot11MultipleRetryCount
dot11MultipleRetryCount.description: This counter shall increment when an MSDU is successfully transmitted after more than one retransmission.

dot11FrameDuplicateCount.name: dot11FrameDuplicateCount
dot11FrameDuplicateCount.description: This counter shall increment when a frame is received that the Sequence Control field indicates is a duplicate.

dot11RTSSuccessCount.name: dot11RTSSuccessCount
dot11RTSSuccessCount.description: This counter shall increment when a CTS is received in response to an RTS.

dot11RTSFailureCount.name: dot11RTSFailureCount
dot11RTSFailureCount.description: This counter shall increment when a CTS is not received in response to an RTS.

dot11ACKFailureCount.name: dot11ACKFailureCount
dot11ACKFailureCount.description: This counter shall increment when an ACK is not received when expected.

dot11ReceivedFragmentCount.name: dot11ReceivedFragmentCount
dot11ReceivedFragmentCount.description: This counter shall be incremented for each successfully received MPDU of type Data or Management.

dot11MulticastReceivedFrameCount.name: dot11MulticastReceivedFrameCount
dot11MulticastReceivedFrameCount.description: This counter shall increment when a MSDU is received with the multicast bit set in the destination MAC address.

dot11FCSErrorCount.name: dot11FCSErrorCount
dot11FCSErrorCount.description: This counter shall increment when an FCS error is detected in a received MPDU.

dot11TransmittedFrameCount.name: dot11TransmittedFrameCount
dot11TransmittedFrameCount.description: This counter shall increment for each successfully transmitted MSDU.

dot11WEPUndecryptableCount.name: dot11WEPUndecryptableCount
dot11WEPUndecryptableCount.description: This counter shall increment when a frame is received with the WEP subfield of the Frame Control field set to one and the WEPOn value for the key mapped to the TA's MAC address indicates that the frame should not have been encrypted or that frame is discarded due to the receiving STA not implementing the privacy option.

dot11GroupAddressesTable.name: dot11GroupAddressesTable
dot11GroupAddressesTable.description: A conceptual table containing a set of MAC addresses identifying the multicast addresses for which this STA will receive frames. The default value of this attribute shall be null.

dot11GroupAddressesEntry.name: dot11GroupAddressesEntry
dot11GroupAddressesEntry.description: An Entry (conceptual row) in the Group Addresses Table. ifIndex - Each IEEE 802.11 interface is represented by an ifEntry. Interface tables in this MIB module are indexed by ifIndex.

dot11GroupAddressesIndex.name: dot11GroupAddressesIndex
dot11GroupAddressesIndex.description: The auxiliary variable used to identify instances of the columnar objects in the Group Addresses Table.

dot11Address.name: dot11Address
dot11Address.description: MAC address identifying a multicast addresses from which this STA will receive frames.

dot11GroupAddressesStatus.name: dot11GroupAddressesStatus
dot11GroupAddressesStatus.description: The status column used for creating, modifying, and deleting instances of the columnar objects in the Group Addresses Table.

dot11ResourceTypeIDName.name: dot11ResourceTypeIDName
dot11ResourceTypeIDName.description: Contains the name of the Resource Type ID managed object. The attribute is read-only and always contains the value RTID. This attribute value shall not be used as a naming attribute for any other managed object class.

dot11ResourceInfoTable.name: dot11ResourceInfoTable
dot11ResourceInfoTable.description: Provides a means of indicating, in data readable from a managed object, information that identifies the source of the implementation.

dot11ResourceInfoEntry.name: dot11ResourceInfoEntry
dot11ResourceInfoEntry.description: An entry in the dot11ResourceInfo Table. ifIndex - Each IEEE 802.11 interface is represented by an ifEntry. Interface tables in this MIB module are indexed by ifIndex.

dot11manufacturerOUI.name: dot11manufacturerOUI
dot11manufacturerOUI.description: Takes the value of an organizationally unique identifier.

dot11manufacturerName.name: dot11manufacturerName
dot11manufacturerName.description: A printable string used to identify the manufacturer of the resource. Maximum string length is 128 octets.

dot11manufacturerProductName.name: dot11manufacturerProductName
dot11manufacturerProductName.description: A printable string used to identify the manufacturer's product name of the resource. Maximum string length is 128 octets.

dot11manufacturerProductVersion.name: dot11manufacturerProductVersion
dot11manufacturerProductVersion.description: Printable string used to identify the manufacturer's product version of the resource. Maximum string length is 128 octets.

dot11PhyOperationTable.name: dot11PhyOperationTable
dot11PhyOperationTable.description: PHY level attributes concerned with operation. Implemented as a table indexed on ifIndex to allow for multiple instantiations on an Agent.

dot11PhyOperationEntry.name: dot11PhyOperationEntry
dot11PhyOperationEntry.description: An entry in the dot11PhyOperation Table. ifIndex - Each IEEE 802.11 interface is represented by an ifEntry. Interface tables in this MIB module are indexed by ifIndex.

dot11PHYType.name: dot11PHYType
dot11PHYType.description: This is an 8-bit integer value that identifies the PHY type supported by the attached PLCP and PMD. Currently defined values and their corresponding PHY types are: FHSS 2.4 GHz = 01 , DSSS 2.4 GHz = 02, IR Baseband = 03, OFDM 5GHz = 04, HRDSSS = 05

dot11CurrentRegDomain.name: dot11CurrentRegDomain
dot11CurrentRegDomain.description: The current regulatory domain this instance of the PMD is supporting. This object corresponds to one of the RegDomains listed in dot11RegDomainsSupported.

dot11TempType.name: dot11TempType
dot11TempType.description: There are different operating temperature requirements dependent on the anticipated environmental conditions. This attribute describes the current PHY's operating temperature range capability. Currently defined values and their corresponding temperature ranges are: Type 1 = X'01'-Commercial range of 0 to 40 degrees C, Type 2 = X'02'-Industrial range of -30 to 70 degrees C.

dot11PhyAntennaTable.name: dot11PhyAntennaTable
dot11PhyAntennaTable.description: Group of attributes for PhyAntenna. Implemented as a table indexed on ifIndex to allow for multiple instances on an agent.

dot11PhyAntennaEntry.name: dot11PhyAntennaEntry
dot11PhyAntennaEntry.description: An entry in the dot11PhyAntenna Table. ifIndex - Each IEEE 802.11 interface is represented by an ifEntry. Interface tables in this MIB module are indexed by ifIndex.

dot11CurrentTxAntenna.name: dot11CurrentTxAntenna
dot11CurrentTxAntenna.description: The current antenna being used to transmit. This value is one of the values appearing in dot11SupportedTxAntenna. This may be used by a management agent to control which antenna is used for transmission.

dot11DiversitySupport.name: dot11DiversitySupport
dot11DiversitySupport.description: This implementation's support for diversity, encoded as: X'01'-diversity is available and is performed over the fixed list of antennas defined in dot11DiversitySelectionRx. X'02'-diversity is not supported. X'03'-diversity is supported and control of diversity is also available, in which case the attribute dot11DiversitySelectionRx can be dynamically modified by the LME.

dot11CurrentRxAntenna.name: dot11CurrentRxAntenna
dot11CurrentRxAntenna.description: The current antenna being used to receive, if the dot11 DiversitySupport indicates that diversity is not supported. The selected antenna shall be one of the antennae marked for receive in the dot11AntennasListTable.

dot11PhyTxPowerTable.name: dot11PhyTxPowerTable
dot11PhyTxPowerTable.description: Group of attributes for dot11PhyTxPowerTable. Implemented as a table indexed on STA ID to allow for multiple instances on an Agent.

dot11PhyTxPowerEntry.name: dot11PhyTxPowerEntry
dot11PhyTxPowerEntry.description: An entry in the dot11PhyTxPower Table. ifIndex - Each IEEE 802.11 interface is represented by an ifEntry. Interface tables in this MIB module are indexed by ifIndex.

dot11NumberSupportedPowerLevels.name: dot11NumberSupportedPowerLevels
dot11NumberSupportedPowerLevels.description: The number of power levels supported by the PMD. This attribute can have a value of 1 to 8.

dot11TxPowerLevel1.name: dot11TxPowerLevel1
dot11TxPowerLevel1.description: The transmit output power for LEVEL1 in mW. This is also the default power level.

dot11TxPowerLevel2.name: dot11TxPowerLevel2
dot11TxPowerLevel2.description: The transmit output power for LEVEL2 in mW.

dot11TxPowerLevel3.name: dot11TxPowerLevel3
dot11TxPowerLevel3.description: The transmit output power for LEVEL3 in mW.

dot11TxPowerLevel4.name: dot11TxPowerLevel4
dot11TxPowerLevel4.description: The transmit output power for LEVEL4 in mW.

dot11TxPowerLevel5.name: dot11TxPowerLevel5
dot11TxPowerLevel5.description: The transmit output power for LEVEL5 in mW.

dot11TxPowerLevel6.name: dot11TxPowerLevel6
dot11TxPowerLevel6.description: The transmit output power for LEVEL6 in mW.

dot11TxPowerLevel7.name: dot11TxPowerLevel7
dot11TxPowerLevel7.description: The transmit output power for LEVEL7 in mW.

dot11TxPowerLevel8.name: dot11TxPowerLevel8
dot11TxPowerLevel8.description: The transmit output power for LEVEL8 in mW.

dot11CurrentTxPowerLevel.name: dot11CurrentTxPowerLevel
dot11CurrentTxPowerLevel.description: The TxPowerLevel N currently being used to transmit data. Some PHYs also use this value to determine the receiver sensitivity requirements for CCA.

dot11PhyFHSSTable.name: dot11PhyFHSSTable
dot11PhyFHSSTable.description: Group of attributes for dot11PhyFHSSTable. Implemented as a table indexed on STA ID to allow for multiple instances on an Agent.

dot11PhyFHSSEntry.name: dot11PhyFHSSEntry
dot11PhyFHSSEntry.description: An entry in the dot11PhyFHSS Table. ifIndex - Each IEEE 802.11 interface is represented by an ifEntry. Interface tables in this MIB module are indexed by ifIndex.

dot11HopTime.name: dot11HopTime
dot11HopTime.description: The time in microseconds for the PMD to change from channel 2 to channel 80.

dot11CurrentChannelNumber.name: dot11CurrentChannelNumber
dot11CurrentChannelNumber.description: The current channel number of the frequency output by the RF synthesizer.

dot11MaxDwellTime.name: dot11MaxDwellTime
dot11MaxDwellTime.description: The maximum time in TU that the transmitter is permitted to operate on a single channel.

dot11CurrentDwellTime.name: dot11CurrentDwellTime
dot11CurrentDwellTime.description: The current time in TU that the transmitter shall operate on a single channel, as set by the MAC. Default is 19 TU.

dot11CurrentSet.name: dot11CurrentSet
dot11CurrentSet.description: The current set of patterns the PLME is using to determine the hopping sequence.

dot11CurrentPattern.name: dot11CurrentPattern
dot11CurrentPattern.description: The current pattern the PLME is using to determine the hop sequence.

dot11CurrentIndex.name: dot11CurrentIndex
dot11CurrentIndex.description: The current index value the PLME is using to determine the CurrentChannelNumber.

dot11EHCCPrimeRadix.name: dot11EHCCPrimeRadix
dot11EHCCPrimeRadix.description: This attribute indicates the value to be used as the prime radix (N) in the HCC and EHCC algorithms.

dot11EHCCNumberofChannelsFamilyIndex.name: dot11EHCCNumberofChannelsFamilyIndex
dot11EHCCNumberofChannelsFamilyIndex.description: This attribute indicates the value to be used as the maximum for the family index (a) in the HCC and EHCC algorithms. The value of this field shall not be less than the prime radix minus 3 (N - 3). The valid range of allowed values is (N - 1), (N - 2), and (N - 3).

dot11EHCCCapabilityImplemented.name: dot11EHCCCapabilityImplemented
dot11EHCCCapabilityImplemented.description: This attribute, when TRUE, indicates that the station implementation is capable of generating the HCC or EHCC algorithms for determining Hopping patterns. The capability is disabled, otherwise. The default value of this attribute is FALSE.

dot11EHCCCapabilityEnabled.name: dot11EHCCCapabilityEnabled
dot11EHCCCapabilityEnabled.description: This attribute, when TRUE, indicates that the capability of the station to operate using the HCC or EHCC algorithms for determining Hopping Patterns is enabled. The capability is disabled, otherwise. The default value of this attribute is FALSE.

dot11HopAlgorithmAdopted.name: dot11HopAlgorithmAdopted
dot11HopAlgorithmAdopted.description: This attribute, indicates which of the algorithms will be used to generate the Hopping Patterns. Valid values are: 1 - hopping patterns as defined in clause 14 2 - hop index method (with or without table) 3 - HCC/EHCC method

dot11RandomTableFlag.name: dot11RandomTableFlag
dot11RandomTableFlag.description: This attribute, indicates that a Random Table is present when the value is True. When the value is False it indicates that a Random Table is not present and that the hop index method is to be used to determine the hopping sequence. The default value of this attribute is True.

dot11NumberofHoppingSets.name: dot11NumberofHoppingSets
dot11NumberofHoppingSets.description: The Number of Sets field indicates the total number of sets within the hopping patterns.

dot11HopModulus.name: dot11HopModulus
dot11HopModulus.description: The number of allowed channels for the hopping set. This is defined by the governing regulatory agency for the country code of the country in which this device is operating.

dot11HopOffset.name: dot11HopOffset
dot11HopOffset.description: The next position in the hopping set.

dot11PhyDSSSTable.name: dot11PhyDSSSTable
dot11PhyDSSSTable.description: Entry of attributes for dot11PhyDSSSEntry. Implemented as a table indexed on ifIndex allow for multiple instances on an Agent.

dot11PhyDSSSEntry.name: dot11PhyDSSSEntry
dot11PhyDSSSEntry.description: An entry in the dot11PhyDSSSEntry Table. ifIndex - Each IEEE 802.11 interface is represented by an ifEntry. Interface tables in this MIB module are indexed by ifIndex.

dot11CurrentChannel.name: dot11CurrentChannel
dot11CurrentChannel.description: The current operating frequency channel of the DSSS PHY. Valid channel numbers are as defined in 15.4.6.2

dot11CCAModeSupported.name: dot11CCAModeSupported
dot11CCAModeSupported.description: dot11CCAModeSupported is a bit-significant value, representing all of the CCA modes supported by the PHY. Valid values are: energy detect only (ED_ONLY) = 01, carrier sense only (CS_ONLY) = 02, carrier sense and energy detect (ED_and_CS)= 04 or the logical sum of any of these values. This attribute shall not be used to indicate the CCA modes supported by a higher rate extension PHY. Rather, the dot11HRCCAModeSupported attribute shall be used to indicate the CCA modes of the higher rate extension PHY.

dot11CurrentCCAMode.name: dot11CurrentCCAMode
dot11CurrentCCAMode.description: The current CCA method in operation. Valid values are: energy detect only (edonly) = 01, carrier sense only (csonly) = 02, carrier sense and energy detect (edandcs)= 04 carrier sense with timer (cswithtimer)= 08 high rate carrier sense and energy detect (hrcsanded)=16.

dot11EDThreshold.name: dot11EDThreshold
dot11EDThreshold.description: The current Energy Detect Threshold being used by the DSSS PHY.

dot11PhyIRTable.name: dot11PhyIRTable
dot11PhyIRTable.description: Group of attributes for dot11PhyIRTable. Implemented as a table indexed on ifIndex to allow for multiple instances on an Agent.

dot11PhyIREntry.name: dot11PhyIREntry
dot11PhyIREntry.description: An entry in the dot11PhyIR Table. ifIndex - Each IEEE 802.11 interface is represented by an ifEntry. Interface tables in this MIB module are indexed by ifIndex.

dot11CCAWatchdogTimerMax.name: dot11CCAWatchdogTimerMax
dot11CCAWatchdogTimerMax.description: This parameter, together with CCAWatchdogCountMax, determines when energy detected in the channel can be ignored.

dot11CCAWatchdogCountMax.name: dot11CCAWatchdogCountMax
dot11CCAWatchdogCountMax.description: This parameter, together with CCAWatchdogTimerMax, determines when energy detected in the channel can be ignored.

dot11CCAWatchdogTimerMin.name: dot11CCAWatchdogTimerMin
dot11CCAWatchdogTimerMin.description: The minimum value to which CCAWatchdogTimerMax can be set.

dot11CCAWatchdogCountMin.name: dot11CCAWatchdogCountMin
dot11CCAWatchdogCountMin.description: The minimum value to which CCAWatchdogCount can be set.

dot11RegDomainsSupportedTable.name: dot11RegDomainsSupportedTable
dot11RegDomainsSupportedTable.description: There are different operational requirements dependent on the regulatory domain. This attribute list describes the regulatory domains the PLCP and PMD support in this implementation. Currently defined values and their corresponding Regulatory Domains are: FCC (USA) = X'10', DOC (Canada) = X'20', ETSI (most of Europe) = X'30', Spain = X'31', France = X'32', MKK (Japan) = X'40', Others = X'00'

dot11RegDomainsSupportedEntry.name: dot11RegDomainsSupportedEntry
dot11RegDomainsSupportedEntry.description: An entry in the dot11RegDomainsSupportedTable. ifIndex - Each IEEE 802.11 interface is represented by an ifEntry. Interface tables in this MIB module are indexed by ifIndex.

dot11RegDomainsSupportedIndex.name: dot11RegDomainsSupportedIndex
dot11RegDomainsSupportedIndex.description: The auxiliary variable used to identify instances of the columnar objects in the RegDomainsSupport Table.

dot11RegDomainsSupportedValue.name: dot11RegDomainsSupportedValue
dot11RegDomainsSupportedValue.description: There are different operational requirements dependent on the regulatory domain. This attribute list describes the regulatory domains the PLCP and PMD support in this implementation. Currently defined values and their corresponding Regulatory Domains are: FCC (USA) = X'10', DOC (Canada) = X'20', ETSI (most of Europe) = X'30', Spain = X'31', France = X'32', MKK (Japan) = X'40'

dot11AntennasListTable.name: dot11AntennasListTable
dot11AntennasListTable.description: This table represents the list of antennae. An antenna can be marked to be capable of transmitting, receiving, and/or for participation in receive diversity. Each entry in this table represents a single antenna with its properties. The maximum number of antennae that can be contained in this table is 255.

dot11AntennasListEntry.name: dot11AntennasListEntry
dot11AntennasListEntry.description: An entry in the dot11AntennasListTable, representing the properties of a single antenna. ifIndex - Each IEEE 802.11 interface is represented by an ifEntry. Interface tables in this MIB module are indexed by ifIndex.

dot11AntennaListIndex.name: dot11AntennaListIndex
dot11AntennaListIndex.description: The unique index of an antenna which is used to identify the columnar objects in the dot11AntennasList Table.

dot11SupportedTxAntenna.name: dot11SupportedTxAntenna
dot11SupportedTxAntenna.description: When true, this object indicates that the antenna represented by dot11AntennaIndex can be used as a transmit antenna.

dot11SupportedRxAntenna.name: dot11SupportedRxAntenna
dot11SupportedRxAntenna.description: When true, this object indicates that the antenna represented by the dot11AntennaIndex xan be used as a receive antenna.

dot11DiversitySelectionRx.name: dot11DiversitySelectionRx
dot11DiversitySelectionRx.description: When true, this object indicates that the antenna represented by dot11AntennaIndex can be used for receive diversity. This object may only be true if the antenna can be used as a receive antenna, as indicated by dot11SupportedRxAntenna.

dot11SupportedDataRatesTxTable.name: dot11SupportedDataRatesTxTable
dot11SupportedDataRatesTxTable.description: The Transmit bit rates supported by the PLCP and PMD, represented by a count from X'02-X'7f, corresponding to data rates in increments of 500kbit/s from 1 Mbit/s to 63.5 Mbit/s subject to limitations of each individual PHY.

dot11SupportedDataRatesTxEntry.name: dot11SupportedDataRatesTxEntry
dot11SupportedDataRatesTxEntry.description: An Entry (conceptual row) in the dot11SupportedDataRatesTx Table. ifIndex - Each IEEE 802.11 interface is represented by an ifEntry. Interface tables in this MIB module are indexed by ifIndex.

dot11SupportedDataRatesTxIndex.name: dot11SupportedDataRatesTxIndex
dot11SupportedDataRatesTxIndex.description: Index object which identifies which data rate to access. Range is 1..8.

dot11SupportedDataRatesTxValue.name: dot11SupportedDataRatesTxValue
dot11SupportedDataRatesTxValue.description: The Transmit bit rates supported by the PLCP and PMD, represented by a count from X'02-X'7f, corresponding to data rates in increments of 500kbit/s from 1 Mbit/s to 63.5 Mbit/s subject to limitations of each individual PHY.

dot11SupportedDataRatesRxTable.name: dot11SupportedDataRatesRxTable
dot11SupportedDataRatesRxTable.description: The receive bit rates supported by the PLCP and PMD, represented by a count from X'002-X'7f, corresponding to data rates in increments of 500kbit/s from 1 Mbit/s to 63.5 Mbit/s.

dot11SupportedDataRatesRxEntry.name: dot11SupportedDataRatesRxEntry
dot11SupportedDataRatesRxEntry.description: An Entry (conceptual row) in the dot11SupportedDataRatesRx Table. ifIndex - Each IEEE 802.11 interface is represented by an ifEntry. Interface tables in this MIB module are indexed by ifIndex.

dot11SupportedDataRatesRxIndex.name: dot11SupportedDataRatesRxIndex
dot11SupportedDataRatesRxIndex.description: Index object which identifies which data rate to access. Range is 1..8.

dot11SupportedDataRatesRxValue.name: dot11SupportedDataRatesRxValue
dot11SupportedDataRatesRxValue.description: The receive bit rates supported by the PLCP and PMD, represented by a count from X'02-X'7f, corresponding to data rates in increments of 500kbit/s from 1 Mbit/s to 63.5 Mbit/s.

dot11PhyOFDMTable.name: dot11PhyOFDMTable
dot11PhyOFDMTable.description: Group of attributes for dot11PhyOFDMTable. Implemented as a table indexed on ifindex to allow for multiple instances on an Agent.

dot11PhyOFDMEntry.name: dot11PhyOFDMEntry
dot11PhyOFDMEntry.description: An entry in the dot11PhyOFDM Table. ifIndex - Each IEEE 802.11 interface is represented by an ifEntry. Interface tables in this MIB module are indexed by ifIndex.

dot11CurrentFrequency.name: dot11CurrentFrequency
dot11CurrentFrequency.description: The number of the current operating frequency channel of the OFDM PHY.

dot11TIThreshold.name: dot11TIThreshold
dot11TIThreshold.description: The Threshold being used to detect a busy medium (frequency). CCA shall report a busy medium upon detecting the RSSI above this threshold.

dot11FrequencyBandsSupported.name: dot11FrequencyBandsSupported
dot11FrequencyBandsSupported.description: The capability of the OFDM PHY implementation to operate in the three U-NII bands. Coded as an integer value of a three bit field as follows: bit 0 .. capable of operating in the lower (5.15-5.25 GHz) U-NII band bit 1 .. capable of operating in the middle (5.25-5.35 GHz) U-NII band bit 2 .. capable of operating in the upper (5.725-5.825 GHz) U-NII band For example, for an implementation capable of operating in the lower and mid bands this attribute would take the value 3.

dot11PhyHRDSSSTable.name: dot11PhyHRDSSSTable
dot11PhyHRDSSSTable.description: Entry of attributes for dot11PhyHRDSSSEntry. Implemented as a table indexed on ifIndex to allow for multiple instances on an Agent.

dot11PhyHRDSSSEntry.name: dot11PhyHRDSSSEntry
dot11PhyHRDSSSEntry.description: An entry in the dot11PhyHRDSSSEntry Table. ifIndex - Each IEEE 802.11 interface is represented by an ifEntry. Interface tables in this MIB module are indexed by ifIndex.

dot11ShortPreambleOptionImplemented.name: dot11ShortPreambleOptionImplemented
dot11ShortPreambleOptionImplemented.description: This attribute, when true, shall indicate that the short preamble option as defined in subclause 18.2.2.2 is implemented. The default value of this attribute shall be false.

dot11PBCCOptionImplemented.name: dot11PBCCOptionImplemented
dot11PBCCOptionImplemented.description: This attribute, when true, shall indicate that the PBCC modulation option as defined in subclause 18.4.6.6 is implemented. The default value of this attribute shall be false.

dot11ChannelAgilityPresent.name: dot11ChannelAgilityPresent
dot11ChannelAgilityPresent.description: This attribute indicates that the PHY is capable of channel agility.

dot11ChannelAgilityEnabled.name: dot11ChannelAgilityEnabled
dot11ChannelAgilityEnabled.description: This attribute indicates that the PHY channel agility functionality is enabled.

dot11HRCCAModeSupported.name: dot11HRCCAModeSupported
dot11HRCCAModeSupported.description: dot11HRCCAModeSupported is a bit-significant value, representing all of the CCA modes supported by the PHY. Valid values are: energy detect only (ED_ONLY) = 01, carrier sense only (CS_ONLY) = 02, carrier sense and energy detect (ED_and_CS)= 04, carrier sense with timer (CS_and_Timer)= 08, high rate carrier sense and energy detect (HRCS_and_ED)= 16 or the logical sum of any of these values. In the high rate extension PHY, this attribute shall be used in preference to the dot11CCAModeSupported attribute.

dot11HoppingPatternTable.name: dot11HoppingPatternTable
dot11HoppingPatternTable.description: The (conceptual) table of attributes necessary for a frequency hopping implementation to be able to create the hopping sequences necessary to operate in the subband for the associated domain country string.

dot11HoppingPatternEntry.name: dot11HoppingPatternEntry
dot11HoppingPatternEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) in the Hopping Pattern Table that indicates the random hopping sequence to be followed. IfIndex - Each IEEE 802.11 interface is represented by an ifEntry. Interface tables in this MIB are indexed by ifIndex.

dot11HoppingPatternIndex.name: dot11HoppingPatternIndex
dot11HoppingPatternIndex.description: The auxiliary variable used to identify instances of the columnar objects in the Hopping Pattern Table.

dot11RandomTableFieldNumber.name: dot11RandomTableFieldNumber
dot11RandomTableFieldNumber.description: This attribute shall indicate the value of the starting channel number in the hopping sequence of the subband for the associated domain country string. The default value of this attribute shall be zero.

dot11Compliance.name: dot11Compliance
dot11Compliance.description: The compliance statement for SNMPv2 entities that implement the IEEE 802.11 MIB.

dot11SMTbase.name: dot11SMTbase
dot11SMTbase.description: The SMT object class provides the necessary support at the STA to manage the processes in the STA such that the STA may work cooperatively as a part of an IEEE 802.11 network.

dot11SMTprivacy.name: dot11SMTprivacy
dot11SMTprivacy.description: The SMTPrivacy package is a set of attributes that shall be present if WEP is implemented in the STA.

dot11MACbase.name: dot11MACbase
dot11MACbase.description: The MAC object class provides the necessary support for the access control, generation, and verification of frame check sequences (FCSs), and proper delivery of valid data to upper layers.

dot11MACStatistics.name: dot11MACStatistics
dot11MACStatistics.description: The MACStatistics package provides extended statistical information on the operation of the MAC. This package is completely optional.

dot11ResourceTypeID.name: dot11ResourceTypeID
dot11ResourceTypeID.description: Attributes used to identify a STA, its manufacturer, and various product names and versions.

dot11PhyAntennaComplianceGroup.name: dot11PhyAntennaComplianceGroup
dot11PhyAntennaComplianceGroup.description: Attributes for Data Rates for IEEE 802.11.

dot11PhyTxPowerComplianceGroup.name: dot11PhyTxPowerComplianceGroup
dot11PhyTxPowerComplianceGroup.description: Attributes for Control and Management of transmit power.

dot11PhyFHSSComplianceGroup.name: dot11PhyFHSSComplianceGroup
dot11PhyFHSSComplianceGroup.description: Attributes that configure the Frequency Hopping for IEEE 802.11.

dot11PhyDSSSComplianceGroup.name: dot11PhyDSSSComplianceGroup
dot11PhyDSSSComplianceGroup.description: Attributes that configure the DSSS for IEEE 802.11.

dot11PhyIRComplianceGroup.name: dot11PhyIRComplianceGroup
dot11PhyIRComplianceGroup.description: Attributes that configure the baseband IR for IEEE 802.11.

dot11PhyRegDomainsSupportGroup.name: dot11PhyRegDomainsSupportGroup
dot11PhyRegDomainsSupportGroup.description: Attributes that specify the supported Regulation Domains.

dot11PhyAntennasListGroup.name: dot11PhyAntennasListGroup
dot11PhyAntennasListGroup.description: Attributes that specify the supported Regulation Domains.

dot11PhyRateGroup.name: dot11PhyRateGroup
dot11PhyRateGroup.description: Attributes for Data Rates for IEEE 802.11.

dot11CountersGroup.name: dot11CountersGroup
dot11CountersGroup.description: Attributes from the dot11CountersGroup that are not described in the dot11MACStatistics group. These objects are mandatory.

dot11SMTbase2.name: dot11SMTbase2
dot11SMTbase2.description: The SMTbase2 object class provides the necessary support at the STA to manage the processes in the STA such that the STA may work cooperatively as a part of an IEEE 802.11 network.

dot11PhyOFDMComplianceGroup.name: dot11PhyOFDMComplianceGroup
dot11PhyOFDMComplianceGroup.description: Attributes that configure the OFDM for IEEE 802.11.

dot11SMTbase3.name: dot11SMTbase3
dot11SMTbase3.description: The SMTbase3 object class provides the necessary support at the STA to manage the processes in the STA such that the STA may work cooperatively as a part of an IEEE 802.11 network, when the STA is capable of multi-domain operation. This object group should be implemented when the multi-domain capability option is implemented.

dot11MultiDomainCapabilityGroup.name: dot11MultiDomainCapabilityGroup
dot11MultiDomainCapabilityGroup.description: The dot11MultiDomainCapabilityGroup object class provides the objects necessary to manage the channels usable by a STA, when the multi-domain capability option is implemented.

dot11PhyFHSSComplianceGroup2.name: dot11PhyFHSSComplianceGroup2
dot11PhyFHSSComplianceGroup2.description: Attributes that configure the Frequency Hopping for IEEE 802.11 when multi-domain capability option is implemented.

dot11PhyHRDSSSComplianceGroup.name: dot11PhyHRDSSSComplianceGroup
dot11PhyHRDSSSComplianceGroup.description: Attributes that configure the HRDSSS for IEEE 802.11.
